1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,247
This is where Sishya becomes Guru.

2
00:00:03,197 --> 00:00:11,736
Look, - SASLSSL is the recommended protocol: SASL provides authentication, SSL provides encryption.

3
00:00:11,736 --> 00:00:23,500
ssl.endpoint.identification.algorithm=https enables hostname verification — never disable this in production.

4
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:32,328
super.users in server.properties bypasses ACLs — restrict to ops accounts only.

5
00:00:32,328 --> 00:00:38,960
Kafka doesn't support row-level security; ACLs operate at the topic level.

6
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:45,644
Fun fact: Uber's solution was distributed event streaming with guaranteed delivery.

7
00:00:45,644 --> 00:00:49,078
That's exactly what we're learning.

8
00:00:49,078 --> 00:00:58,565
I watched a candidate explain this perfectly and get a 45 LPA offer at a top product company in Bangalore.

9
00:00:58,565 --> 00:01:03,184
Same concept, same interview room, same question.

